modules.description: Provides functions for initializing audio devices, playing audio data, and managing audio formats. Works with raw audio buffers, sample rates, and channel configurations. Used to output sound from OCaml applications across multiple platforms.

Provides functions to retrieve and manage audio drivers, open audio devices for playback, and control audio output. Works with driver metadata, audio configuration parameters, and audio buffer data. Used to select and configure audio output drivers, open live or file-based audio streams, and play audio data through specified devices.
